                        <div style="margin-top: 6px">Moreover, if youre going to die, you can opt to kill a <i>Proxy</i> instead. This is not guaranteed; make the same low-dice determination, and if the loser isnt you, a <i>Proxy</i> dies instead (usually with no visible cause) and you lose half your current health. Doing this jerk-ass move is a Violence-8 check, and breaks the all your <i>Proxy</i> bonds. Presumably, the cosmos thinks all of them died? Proxy isnt just sticky, its permanent until magick or death removes it.</div>
